    "---\n",
    "## 🐍 A. Sintaxis Python — Tipos básicos\n",
    "| Tipo | Ejemplo | Función |\n",
    "|------|---------|---------|\n",
    "| `int` | `x = 42` | Números enteros |\n",
    "| `float` | `x = 3.14` | Decimales |\n",
    "| `str` | `s = 'hola'` | Texto |\n",
    "| `bool` | `b = True` | Verdadero/Falso |\n",
    "| `list` | `l = [1, 2, 3]` | Lista mutable |\n",
    "| `tuple` | `t = (1, 2)` | Tupla inmutable |\n",
    "| `dict` | `d = {'a': 1}` | Llave → valor |\n",
    "| `set` | `s = {1, 2}` | Conjunto único |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## ➗ B. Operadores\n",
    "### Aritméticos: `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `//` (div entera), `%` (módulo), `**` (potencia)\n",
    "### Comparación: `==`, `!=`, `<`, `>`, `<=`, `>=`\n",
    "### Lógicos: `and`, `or`, `not`\n",
    "### Identidad: `is`, `is not` (comparan objetos, no valores)\n",
    "### Pertenencia: `in`, `not in`\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# Boolean trick: reemplaza if/else con aritmética\n",
    "# En vez de:\n",
    "if sexo == 'hombre':\n",
    "    calorias = 66 + (13.7 * peso)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    calorias = 655 + (9.6 * peso)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Usa:\n",
    "es_hombre = (sexo == 'hombre')  # True=1, False=0\n",
    "calorias = es_hombre * (66 + 13.7*peso) + (1-es_hombre) * (655 + 9.6*peso)\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 🔤 C. Strings — Slicing\n",
    "```python\n",
    "s = 'Python'\n",
    "s[0]    → 'P'           # primer carácter\n",
    "s[-1]   → 'n'           # último\n",
    "s[1:4]  → 'yth'         # del índice 1 al 3 (excluye 4)\n",
    "s[:3]   → 'Pyt'         # primeros 3\n",
    "s[3:]   → 'hon'         # desde el 3 en adelante\n",
    "s[::-1] → 'nohtyP'      # invertido\n",
    "s[::2]  → 'Pto'         # cada 2 caracteres\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📦 D. Estructuras de Datos\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# Listas\n",
    "nums = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5]\n",
    "nums.append(9)      # → [3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9]\n",
    "nums.sort()         # → [1, 1, 3, 4, 5, 9]\n",
    "nums.pop()          # → 9, nums es [1, 1, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "# List comprehension\n",
    "pares = [x for x in range(10) if x % 2 == 0]  # → [0, 2, 4, 6, 8]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Diccionarios\n",
    "edades = {'Ana': 25, 'Luis': 30}\n",
    "edades.get('Ana', 0)     # → 25 (o 0 si no existe)\n",
    "edades.keys()            # → ['Ana', 'Luis']\n",
    "edades.values()          # → [25, 30]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sets\n",
    "a = {1, 2, 3}; b = {3, 4, 5}\n",
    "a & b  # intersección → {3}\n",
    "a | b  # unión       → {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}\n",
    "a - b  # diferencia   → {1, 2}\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 🔢 E. NumPy — Referencia Rápida\n",
    "```python\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "a = np.array([1, 2, 3])       # crear array 1D\n",
    "b = np.zeros((3, 4))          # matriz 3×4 de ceros\n",
    "c = np.ones((2, 3))           # matriz 2×3 de unos\n",
    "d = np.random.rand(3, 3)      # valores aleatorios [0,1)\n",
    "e = np.linspace(0, 1, 5)      # → [0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]\n",
    "\n",
    "a.shape          # → (3,)\n",
    "b.reshape(2, 6)  # cambiar forma\n",
    "a.mean()         # promedio\n",
    "a.std()          # desviación estándar\n",
    "a.max()          # valor máximo\n",
    "\n",
    "# Indexación booleana\n",
    "a[a > 2]  # → [3]\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
